      • PlayerStatistic

        public PlayerStatistic(java.util.UUID uuid,
                       java.lang.String userid,
                       java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> plainStatistics,
                       java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<org.bukkit.Material,java.lang.Integer>> materialStatistics,
                       java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<org.bukkit.entity.EntityType,java.lang.Integer>> entityStatistics)
        This is the constructor used for creating a new PlayerStatistic object for a player who already has existing statistics
        Parameters:
        uuid - the uuid of the player this object will be destined to
        userid - another, shorter id of the player, which is used internally to access data from the SQL-Database
        plainStatistics - a map of all statistics which have no (NONE) Substatistic
        materialStatistics - a map of all statistics which have a MATERIAL Substatistic
        entityStatistics - a map of all statistics which have an ENTITY Substatistic
